<subSubSection id="C3213283FFA1F925FF5BFB53FE53FADF" pageId="51" pageNumber="248" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B846108FFA1F925FF5BFB53FB65FB1A" blockId="51.[151,1436,989,1393]" box="[196,1279,1177,1204]" pageId="51" pageNumber="248">
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFA1F925FF5BFB53FEB5FB1D" bold="true" box="[196,303,1177,1203]" pageId="51" pageNumber="248">Ecology.</emphasis>
Psammophilous species occurring in the same habitats as the other 
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFA1F925FBD5FB50FB01FB1D" box="[1098,1179,1178,1203]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="248">Nessus</emphasis>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B846108FFA1F925FF5BFB75FE53FADF" blockId="51.[151,1436,989,1393]" pageId="51" pageNumber="248">
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFA1F925FF5BFB75FE8BFB77" bold="true" box="[196,273,1215,1241]" pageId="51" pageNumber="248">Notes.</emphasis>
In 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA1CF9FFA1F925FED0FB0AFD0CFB74" author="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P." box="[335,662,1216,1242]" pageId="51" pageNumber="248" pagination="173 - 175" refId="ref75329" refString="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P. (2005) Insecta Coleoptera Histeridae. In: Ruffo, S. &amp; Stoch, F. (Eds), Checklist e distribuzione della fauna italiana. Memorie del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 2. serie, Sezione Scienze della Vita, 16, pp. 173 - 175, with data on CD-ROM." type="journal article" year="2005">Penati and Vienna (2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA1CF9FFA1F925FD32FB0AFD6CFB74" author="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P." box="[685,758,1216,1242]" pageId="51" pageNumber="248" pagination="173 - 175" refId="ref75399" refString="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P. (2006 a) Insecta Coleoptera Histeridae. In: Ruffo, S. &amp; Stoch, F. (Eds), Checklist and distribution of the Italian fauna. Memorie del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 2. serie, Sezione Scienze della Vita, 17, pp. 173 - 175, with data on CD-ROM." type="journal article" year="2006">2006a</bibRefCitation>
) the specimen from Oristano (CUL) is ascribed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B1A8BFFA1F925FF08FB2CFD80FB51" baseAuthorityName="Erichson" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[151,538,1253,1279]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Hypocacculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubripes" subGenus="Nessus">
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFA1F925FF08FB2CFEA7FB51" box="[151,317,1254,1279]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="248">Hypocacculus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFA1F925FECEFB2CFE38FB51" box="[337,418,1254,1279]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="248">Nessus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFA1F925FE28FB2CFD80FB51" box="[439,538,1254,1279]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="248">rubripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its label data are erroneously given as “Assemini, 1940, coll. Museo Genova” (see “Data collection”). Because it is a male, the dissection of the aedeagus allowed me to identify it as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B1A8BFFA1F925FF29FAFBFEB0FAE4" authorityName="Yelamos" authorityYear="1992" box="[182,298,1329,1355]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Hypocacculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferreri">
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFA1F925FF29FAFBFF51FAE4" box="[182,203,1329,1354]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="248">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFA1F925FF46FAFBFEB0FAE4" box="[217,298,1329,1354]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="248">ferreri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFA1F925FEB5FAFBFEB4FAE4" box="[298,302,1329,1354]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="248">.</emphasis>
This is the second record for this species from the island, and a confirmation of what stated in the notes under 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B1A8BFFA1F925FEB9FA9DFE58FADE" authorityName="Reichardt" authorityYear="1932" box="[294,450,1367,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Histeridae" genus="Hypocacculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ascendens">
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFA1F925FEB9FA9DFEA1FADE" box="[294,315,1367,1392]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="248">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFA1F925FED5FA9DFE58FADE" box="[330,450,1367,1392]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="248">ascendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
